 ."],"variants":[{"name":"Pook","meanings":["English (mainly Devon): nickname from Middle English <i>p(o)uk(e)</i>, <i>poke</i> ‘goblin, (evil or mischievous) spirit’ (Old English <i>pūca</i>)."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Apuke was born in 1460, in England, his father, Thomas Apuke, was 25 and his mother, Apuke, was 21. He had at least 1 son with Catherine Alice Baldwin. He died in 1507, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1460–1507":"1460–1507","1456–1561":"1456–1561","1487–1559":"1487–1559","1435–1506":"1435–1506","1440–Female":"1440–Surnud","1435":"1435","1456":"1456","1487":"1487","1440":"1440","1561":"1561","1460":"1460","22 September 1506":"22. september 1506","1507":"1507","1506":"1506","1559":"1559","England":"England","Aston Clinton, Buckinghamshire, England":"Aston Clinton, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1460–1507":"1460–1507","1456–1561":"1456–1561","1487–1559":"1487–1559","1435–1506":"1435–1506","1440–Female":"1440–Kuollut","1435":"1435","1456":"1456","1487":"1487","1440":"1440","1561":"1561","1460":"1460","22 September 1506":"22. syyskuuta 1506","1507":"1507","1506":"1506","1559":"1559","England":"England","Aston Clinton, Buckinghamshire, England":"Aston Clinton, Buckinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1460–1507":"1460–1507","1456–1561":"1456–1561","1487–1559":"1487–1559","1435–1506":"1435–1506","1440–Female":"1440–Décédée","1435":"1435","1456":"1456","1487":"1487","1440":"1440","1561":"1561","1460":"1460","22 September 1506":"22 septemb